   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>e. The Word of God Growing</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>and the Number of the Disciples Multiplying Greatly</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>According to the record in the book of Acts, the word of God grew, and the number of the disciples multiplied greatly 6:7; 12:24; 19:20 .</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>f.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The Disciples Being Scattered</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>from Jerusalem to Preach the Gospel</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>throughout the Regions of Judea and Samaria</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The disciples were scattered from Jerusalem throughout the regions of Judea and Samaria.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Those who were scattered went throughout the land preaching the gospel Acts 8:1, 4 .</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>g. The Gospel Spreading under Peter's Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In Acts 9:32-43 we see that the gospel spread under Peter's ministry.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>h.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The Gospel, through Paul's Ministry,</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Spreading to the Gentile World,</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>and Many Churches Being Raised Up</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Through Paul's ministry the gospel spread to the Gentile world, and many churches were raised up Acts 13 28 .</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>i.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The Churches Raised Up through Paul's Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Being Strengthened and Corrected</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>under John's Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The Epistles of 1, 2, and 3 John and the book of Revelation show us that the churches raised up through Paul's ministry were strengthened and corrected under John's ministry.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The Satanic Chaos</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Again the satanic chaos was unavoidable and went along with the divine economy in the ministry of the apostles.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>This chaos includes twenty-six items.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>a. The Jewish Religion and the Roman Government</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Persecuting the Apostles and the Church</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The Jewish religion and the Roman government persecuted the apostles and the church Acts 4:1-3, 5-6; 7:57 8:3; 12:1-4; 16:22-24 .</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Religion and politics often collaborate to persecute and damage the Lord's interest on earth.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>b.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Ananias and Sapphira Deceiving the Spirit</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>and Being Punished to Death</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>In Acts 5:1-11 Ananias, a brother, and his wife Sapphira deceived the Spirit and were punished to death in the presence of the church.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>That surely was something of chaos.</S>
   </TEXT>
